 country's laws and protecting citizens' human rights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aHuman rightszSouth Africa. 0aLaw enforcementzSouth AfricazJohannesburg. 0aProstitutionxLaw and legislationzSouth Africa. 0aProstitutionzSouth AfricazJohannesburg. 0aSex workersxLegal status, laws, etc.zSouth Africa. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh  a(de)criminalization.  acriminal law.  aethnography.  afeminism.  agender.  ahuman rights.  apolicing of sex.  aprostitution.  asex work.  asexuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362975240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503629752423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503629752/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles